The skepticism we possess that we’ve presumed to be “rational thinking” & an objective assessment of factual data about yourself, is rooted in actual mental junk.

Your doubts are not the product of accurate thinking, but habitual thinking. Years ago you accepted flawed conclusions as correct, began to live your life as if those warped ideas about your potential were true, and ceases the bold experiment in living that brought you many breakthrough behaviors as a child.

Now it’s time for you to find that faith you had in yourself before.

Suspend disbelief.

ACT like you have complete faith. Merely do what your do if you knew you were going to succeed. Behave like you have that total conviction.

If you must doubt something, doubt your limits 💯🤍

#You2 #quantumleaps #gogetit #explorepage #inspo

this years been rough in so many ways..i never would have envisioned my life would turn out the way that it has at *almost 37 years old..and the hardest part of it all is keeping everything in perspective and never comparing my own journey to that of others.

i’ve kept my struggles very private, & haven’t shared much on socials as i’ve been navigating really my life as a whole..

last night we celebrated a new era and for the first time in a long time i felt ignited, encouraged, & like i’m truly stepping into my OWN again & it feels so good.💚

changes can happen in an instant, literally. i hope that if you find yourself in a valley, you always remember that, & always keep the faith that God has a beautiful plan for your life. when you have no idea how to get through it, He has the plan to it, remember that!

✨chapter 37✨
thank you so much for all the love, calls, texts, posts, and sweet messages. y’all really know how to make a girl feel so loved❤️ i appreciate everyone who took the time out of their days to wish me a happy birthday! it truly means the world to me.🫶

today i stepped into a new realm of a career path that i couldn’t be more excited for. i felt all the emotions today on my first day, nervous, excited, and so much peace and anticipation for my future.

it’s scary stepping into something new, and as i’ve been marinating on that the past week, i’ve also been reminded of everything that i’ve been blessed with in the past decade and especially the past 4 years. what I’ve chosen to focus on is the fact that everything in my life currently is a result of what i’ve made a decision on to possess or embody. it’s a result of my best thinking. this serves as such a great reminder in this season and in life, period..that we truly only get what we want and are determined to have in this life. so instead of focusing on the fears of what “may (and typically does not) happen”, let us all focus on the limitless possibilities and what we truly desire.

love y’all bigly
🤍

your journey is your own..between you and our Creator. not one human has the authority to dictate or have an opinion about the path that you are on in your life.

people will always have their opinions on what they they think is best for you, & if you choose a different path they may think less of you.. and that’s on them, not you.

i’ve spent far too much time worrying about what certain people will think about my personal decisions..which had lead to a lack of confidence in my own judgment there for a minute.

i’ve had to re-learn self-validation & trusting in my own decision making abilities. and constantly reminding myself that i am the one who knows myself best..my own circumstances, values, and aspirations.

we unlock a new level of freedom when we choose to walk our own path, without the fear of others opinions or allowing others to dictate the direction of our lives.

self-validation is one of the greatest forms of self-love🤍

i have fought to become the woman who loves myself for everything i am, flaws and all. to not seek outside validation and approval from man.

i’ve struggled with body image and being “good enough”, “fit enough”, etc for as long as i can remember. so many of us struggle with that as women.. and i’m telling you the greatest gift we can give ourselves is the gift of self love and appreciating our bodies for everything they are, just as they are. you alone, just as you are, is the capable, powerful, beautiful, amazing woman who is perfect, whole and complete. 🫶

i strive to be the best version of me, but i’m becoming proud of the woman i am today who knows that i am enough, just as i am. and i pray that if you aren’t there yet, you realize that you too are perfectly imperfect, worthy and beautiful, just as you are.💕

you’re under zero obligation to be who you were yesterday or moment to moment. 
you can switch it up at any moment and you owe no one anything.
do you bb🤍

choose joy.

i don’t believe in the saying that “everything happens for a reason”…there’s many unfortunate events that occur where any “reason” couldn’t be justified.

but i do believe that everything that happens in life is meant to teach us something. there’s always an opportunity for growth attached to the events that happen in our lives, that can shape us and mold us if we allow them to.

choosing joy and peace, and clinging to the One who created you who brings hope and clarity in our circumstances is what i will cling to always.

our God is a sovereign and loving God who has the most beautiful plans for our lives. we discover this through the growth of our circumstances and the knowing that He has our backs through it all and will never forsake us.

Rule #27
be so confident in God’s plan that you don’t even get upset anymore when things don’t go your way.🤍

i met a woman today in the sauna that happened to be a God appointment. she told me, “no matter what you’re going through, thank God in advance for what He’s about to do, always.” we both landed in the same place at the same time, on purpose. through conversation we both learned how parallel our lives were in this exact moment. it was such a sweet reminder to me how God orchestrates divine appointments and how He truly looks out for us and is so personal.

i want to pass this same encouragement on to you..no matter what you’re going through, thank Him in advance for what He’s about to do. stay faithful.🤍
